HEADWORD: Bondman
<hw>Bond"man</hw> <pr>(-m⟦ait⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Bondmen</plw> <pr>(-m⟦eit⟧n)</pr>.</plu>
<ety>[<ets>Bond</ets>,<pos>a.</pos>or<pos>n.</pos>+
<ets>man</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A man slave, or one bound to
service without wages.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧To enfranchise
<xex>bondmen</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Macaulay.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Old Eng. Law)</fld> <def>A villain, or tenant in
villenage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bond servant</ent>⟦br⟧
